{
  "texts": [
    "PragMetis enables users to express context-dependent flow facts through user-defined abstractions, enhancing the portability and reusability of the analysis across different hardware platforms.",
    "This tool uses Control-Flow Relation Graphs (CFRGs) to transfer these facts to the machine-code level, ensuring accuracy even with compiler optimizations.",
    "PragMetis addresses the limitations of traditional WCET tools that operate at the binary level and require error-prone, labor-intensive machine-code annotations.",
    "By providing expressive source-level annotations, PragMetis enhances maintainability and reduces the need for manual binary-level annotations.",
    "It supports complex inter-component path dependencies and leverages opportunistic annotations to aggregate flow facts, enabling more precise WCET bounds."
  ]
}